#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.136"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.136:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.136:0.2"
msgid "14. Rājavagga"
msgstr "14. Kings"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.136:0.3"
msgid "136. Dutiyapatthanāsutta"
msgstr "136. Aspiration (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: oparajjaṃ → uparajjaṃ (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.136:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa "
"jeṭṭho putto oparajjaṃ pattheti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, an anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son with five factors "
"aspires to become a viceroy."

msgctxt "an5.136:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.136:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto ubhato "
"sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā "
"pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when an anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son is well born on both "
"his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable "
"in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation."

msgctxt "an5.136:1.4"
msgid ""
"abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato;"
msgstr "He is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty."

msgctxt "an5.136:1.5"
msgid "mātāpitūnaṃ piyo hoti manāpo, balakāyassa piyo hoti manāpo;"
msgstr ""
"He is dear and beloved to his parents. He is dear and beloved to the armed "
"forces."

msgctxt "an5.136:1.6"
msgid ""
"paṇḍito hoti viyatto medhāvī paṭibalo atītānāgatapaccuppanne atthe cintetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"He is astute, competent, and intelligent, able to think issues through as "
"they bear upon the past, future, and present."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.155"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.136:2.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "an5.136:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ khomhi ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva "
"sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena."
msgstr "‘I’m well born …"

msgctxt "an5.136:2.3"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.136:2.4"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya "
"samannāgato."
msgstr "attractive …"

msgctxt "an5.136:2.5"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.136:2.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ khomhi mātāpitūnaṃ piyo manāpo."
msgstr "dear and beloved to my parents …"

msgctxt "an5.136:2.7"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.136:2.8"
msgid "Ahaṃ khomhi balakāyassa piyo manāpo."
msgstr "dear and beloved to the armed forces …"

msgctxt "an5.136:2.9"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.136:2.10"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī paṭibalo atītānāgatapaccuppanne atthe "
"cintetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"I’m astute, competent, and intelligent, able to think issues through as they "
"bear upon the past, future, and present."

msgctxt "an5.136:2.11"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to become a viceroy?’"

msgctxt "an5.136:2.12"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño khattiyassa "
"muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto oparajjaṃ pattheti."
msgstr ""
"An anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son with these five factors aspires "
"to become a viceroy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.136:3.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āsavānaṃ "
"khayaṃ pattheti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities aspires to end the "
"defilements."

msgctxt "an5.136:3.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.136:3.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, and has "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an5.136:3.4"
msgid "bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with "
"right view."

#. VAR: suppatiṭṭhitacitto → supaṭṭhitacitto (bj, s1-3) | supatiṭṭhitacitto (pts1) | sūpaṭṭhitacitto (mr)
msgctxt "an5.136:3.5"
msgid "catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto hoti;"
msgstr ""
"Their mind is firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "an5.136:3.6"
msgid ""
"āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu;"
msgstr ""
"They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and "
"gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking "
"off when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "an5.136:3.7"
msgid ""
"paññavā hoti, udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya "
"sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is "
"noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.156"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.136:4.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an5.136:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ khomhi sīlavā, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharāmi ācāragocarasampanno "
"aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhāmi sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr "‘I’m ethical …"

msgctxt "an5.136:4.3"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ → sātthā sabyañjanā (bj)
#. VAR: dhātā → dhatā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.136:4.4"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi bahussuto sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā "
"majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpā me dhammā bahussutā honti "
"dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā."
msgstr "learned …"

msgctxt "an5.136:4.5"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.136:4.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ khomhi catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto."
msgstr "mindful …"

msgctxt "an5.136:4.7"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.136:4.8"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi āraddhavīriyo viharāmi akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ "
"dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu "
"dhammesu."
msgstr "energetic …"

msgctxt "an5.136:4.9"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.136:4.10"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi paññavā udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya "
"nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"wise. I have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, "
"penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering."

msgctxt "an5.136:4.11"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?’"

msgctxt "an5.136:4.12"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ "
"patthetī”ti."
msgstr "A mendicant with these five qualities aspires to end the defilements.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.136:4.13"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
